<%- include('partials/head') %>

<section class="home-hero">
  <div class="home-hero-inner">
    <div class="home-hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">skydesign.com.au</p>
      <h1>Find cheap flight deals from Australia</h1>
      <p>Search cached Travelpayouts fares, compare route ideas, and continue to live Aviasales search when cached prices are not available.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="home-search-panel">
      <%- include('partials/search-form', {
        formId: 'home-flight-search',
        formAction: '/api/flight-prices',
        formMethod: 'get',
        formClass: 'home-search-form',
        buttonText: 'Search deals'
      }) %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="home-results-section" id="home-results" aria-live="polite" hidden>
  <div class="section-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">Cached fares</p>
    <h2 id="home-results-title">Flight deal results</h2>
    <p id="home-results-note">Cached fares may change when you continue to the booking partner.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="home-message" id="home-results-message" hidden></div>
  <div class="deal-grid" id="home-deal-grid"></div>
  <div class="home-fallback" id="home-fallback" hidden>
    <a class="button button-primary" id="home-fallback-link" href="/flight-deal-finder">Continue to live search</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="home-results-section" id="home-popular-results" aria-live="polite" hidden>
  <div class="section-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">Popular cached deals</p>
    <h2>Broader month-level options</h2>
    <p>These cached fares come from broader month-level Travelpayouts searches.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="deal-grid" id="home-popular-grid"></div>
</section>

<section class="band">
  <div class="section-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">Popular flight deals</p>
    <h2>Start with common routes from Australia</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="popular-route-grid">
    <article class="popular-route-card" data-origin="SYD" data-destination="DPS">
      <h3>Sydney to Bali</h3>
      <p>Search cached fares from Sydney to Denpasar for beach holidays and flexible travel dates.</p>
      <button class="button button-secondary popular-search-button" type="button">Search deals</button>
    </article>
    <article class="popular-route-card" data-origin="SYD" data-destination="MEL">
      <h3>Sydney to Melbourne</h3>
      <p>Compare short-hop domestic fares between Australia's busiest city pair.</p>
      <button class="button button-secondary popular-search-button" type="button">Search deals</button>
    </article>
    <article class="popular-route-card" data-origin="SYD" data-destination="DXB">
      <h3>Sydney to Dubai</h3>
      <p>Look for cached long-haul fares and one-stop options from Sydney to Dubai.</p>
      <button class="button button-secondary popular-search-button" type="button">Search deals</button>
    </article>
    <article class="popular-route-card" data-origin="MEL" data-destination="DPS">
      <h3>Melbourne to Bali</h3>
      <p>Find cached Bali fare ideas from Melbourne for popular holiday periods.</p>
      <button class="button button-secondary popular-search-button" type="button">Search deals</button>
    </article>
    <article class="popular-route-card" data-origin="MEL" data-destination="SIN">
      <h3>Melbourne to Singapore</h3>
      <p>Search cached fares to Singapore for stopovers, business trips, and holidays.</p>
      <button class="button button-secondary popular-search-button" type="button">Search deals</button>
    </article>
    <article class="popular-route-card" data-origin="SYD" data-destination="BKK">
      <h3>Sydney to Bangkok</h3>
      <p>Explore cached Thailand fares from Sydney and continue to live search when needed.</p>
      <button class="button button-secondary popular-search-button" type="button">Search deals</button>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="seo-section">
  <div class="section-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">Cheap flights from Australia</p>
    <h2>Search smarter before you book</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="seo-grid">
    <article>
      <h3>Cheap flights from Australia</h3>
      <p>SkyDesign helps Australian travellers start with cached fare data, then move to live affiliate search for current availability and final pricing.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Popular destinations</h3>
      <p>Start with high-demand routes including Bali, Melbourne, Dubai, Singapore, and Bangkok, then adjust dates to compare fare patterns.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>How SkyDesign flight search works</h3>
      <p>The app asks the backend for cached Travelpayouts prices. If cached fares exist, they appear as deal cards with View Deal buttons.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Cached prices note</h3>
      <p>Travelpayouts data is cache-based. Empty results are normal, so SkyDesign always keeps a live Aviasales fallback search available.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="section-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
    <h2>Flight search questions</h2>
  </div>
  <details>
    <summary>Are cached prices final booking prices?</summary>
    <p>No. Cached prices are useful fare signals, but final price and availability are confirmed on the booking partner's live search page.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>What happens when no cached price is available?</summary>
    <p>SkyDesign shows a live Aviasales affiliate search button so you can continue checking the latest fares.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary>Are API keys exposed in the browser?</summary>
    <p>No. Travelpayouts API requests run through the Express backend. The frontend receives only sanitized results and affiliate links.</p>
  </details>
</section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
